verbose_text: Antipsychotic naive FEP is associated with elevated fasting glucose, glucose following the oral glucose tolerance test, fasting insulin, and insulin resistance (effect size range 0.20-0.61), raised triglycerides (effect size : 0.14), and reduced total cholesterol and LDL cholesterol (effect size range : -0.22 to -0.19).
evidence: insulin resistance (effect size range 0.20-0.61), raised triglycerides (effect size: 0.14), and reduced total cholesterol and LDL cholesterol
